HEADWORD: Wheelhouse
<hw>Wheel"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small house on or above a vessel's deck, containing
the steering wheel.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def> A paddle box. See under
<er>Paddle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheeling</ent>⟦br⟧
